column87: 1. How is the recruiting process like for international jobs? Is it separate? Do you have to be fluent in the language of the country you want to work in or does it depend on the job / organization?    2. Was it worth it? I'm in finance and many of my finance peers remind me that it will be $200k+ for tuition, board, travel and entertainment on top of $200-$400k opportunity loss in salary. In addition, you lose 2 years of work experience.    3. If my long-term career goal is to start a start-up company in social / mobile gaming or some other start-up venture, do you think getting an MBA will help? Do you think building a strong network helps with start-ups?
Exit Opps, Admission tips
Whats the main reason you pursued your MBA?    Whats the greatest benefit you got from your MBA experience?    Do you feel the MBA has paid off for you considering where you are now in your career?
1. How to switch from Accounting to Finance  2. Full time MBA vs Part time MBA  3. Career track in finance/accounting industry.
Is it worth it?  When would I be ready to apply for a program?  Did the degree help you achieve your goals?
Worth costs? Which schools? EMBA?

Pieces of advice that incoming students should know before starting their first semester?    How important are classes in relation to all other program activities? Was it difficult to balance?    What was the job search like? (Especially in regards to non-traditional career paths)
1. Did you consider a Master and why finally an MBA over it?  2. What career change or benefit came about after you graduated?  3. Do employers ask for your GPA?
Motivation for pursuing MBA?  How did you choose your respective school?  Steps taken taken for non-traditional recruitment process (ie buyside work at a VC firm)

1) What do you feel are the greatest skills/lessons you have learned/obtained through your MBA experience?  2) What differentiates your school from others?  3) What is one thing you wish you knew before you entered business school?
Why did you decide to get an MBA?  What was the most valuable thing you learned at B-school?  How does b-school help you achiever your career goals?
1. Part time program vs Full time program  2. Programs available in NY area  3. GMAT avg scores in schools in NY
COST, JOB, promotion
(1)How much for join the MBA program.  (2)What's the specific benefits of MBA to your future career?  (3)Does MBA really help you find better job in the job market?
1) How did attending your school affect your career?  2) How were you able to finance your MBA?  3) Where else did you apply and why did you choose the school?  3)

If you were to start the MBA year over again, how would you approach it differently? What would you do in the months before you start?    How much should I be budgeting for all of these extra trips that folks take during the MBA?    What areas outside of banking are good jobs to look into, if we are concerned about getting an ROI on your bschool investment?
What kind of working experience is good for MBA application?

How important is MBA in terms of promotion.  Do compnay insist on MBA degree only when it comes to hiring high level position such as trader?  How much difference it makes which MBA school you graduated from?
Why did you choose your school/program? What is the top bit of advice you would give for prospective applicants? What parts of the MBA experience did you value most?
